<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF3AFF70A7ADFBB9FCF4D955" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF3AFF70A7ADFBB9FEF0D871" blockId="163.[189,310,1110,1136]" box="[189,310,1110,1136]" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF3AFF70A7ADFBB9FEF0D871" bold="true" box="[189,310,1110,1136]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF3AFF70A7ADFBB9FEF0D871" bold="true" box="[189,310,1110,1136]" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF3AFF70A7ADFB69FCF4D955" blockId="163.[189,1399,1158,1364]" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
This species may be separated from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF3AFF70A448FB69FC03D8A1" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[856,965,1158,1184]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF3AFF70A448FB69FC03D8A1" box="[856,965,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Charinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Oceania as follows: aside from 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF3AFF70A7ADFB45FE96D8C5" authorityName="Weygoldt" authorityYear="2006" box="[189,336,1194,1220]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuanus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF3AFF70A7ADFB45FE96D8C5" box="[189,336,1194,1220]" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">C. papuanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only other charinid species in the region in which the first tarsal article of leg I is as long as the sum of the next five articles is 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF3AFF70A567FB21FD33D8E9" authorityName="Dunn" authorityYear="1949" box="[631,757,1230,1256]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pescotti">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF3AFF70A567FB21FD33D8E9" box="[631,757,1230,1256]" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">C. pescotti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF3AFF70A487FB21FBEAD8E9" authorityName="Weygoldt" authorityYear="2006" box="[919,1068,1230,1256]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuanus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF3AFF70A487FB21FBEAD8E9" box="[919,1068,1230,1256]" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">C. papuanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the number of dorsal spines on the pedipalp femur. 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF3AFF70A5FBFB1DFC17D90D" authorityName="Weygoldt" authorityYear="2006" box="[747,977,1266,1292]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuanus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF3AFF70A5FBFB1DFC17D90D" box="[747,977,1266,1292]" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Charinus papuanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs further from 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF3AFF70A3D2FB1CFAB1D90D" baseAuthorityName="L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[1218,1399,1266,1293]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australianus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF3AFF70A3D2FB1CFAB1D90D" box="[1218,1399,1266,1293]" italics="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">C. australianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other New Caledonian species by the presence of a setiferous tubercle instead of a spine between ventral spine 1 and the proximal margin of the femur.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF3AFF70A7ADFA92FECCD9EA" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF3AFF70A7ADFA92FE82D996" blockId="163.[189,324,1405,1431]" box="[189,324,1405,1431]" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF3AFF70A7ADFA92FE82D996" bold="true" box="[189,324,1405,1431]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF3AFF70A7ADFA92FE82D996" bold="true" box="[189,324,1405,1431]" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF3AFF70A7ADFA43FECCD9EA" blockId="163.[189,1398,1452,1515]" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">
Adjective referring to 
<collectingCountry id="7FFDE2F3FF3AFF70A6D5FA42FD6AD9C7" box="[453,684,1452,1479]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
, the country in which the 
<typeStatus id="D8511CC1FF3AFF70A4F1FA42FBD2D9C6" box="[993,1044,1453,1479]" pageId="163" pageNumber="164">type</typeStatus>
locality is situated (
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF3AFF70A213FA43FF38D9EA" author="Weygoldt P." firstAuthor="Weygoldt" journalOrPublisher="Zoologischer Anzeiger" pageId="163" pageNumber="164" pagination="239 - 247" part="244" refId="ref156278" refString="Weygoldt P. 2006 a. Courtship and sperm transfer in Charinus neocaledonicus Kraepelin, 1895 and Charinus australianus (L. Koch, 1867) (Arachnida, Amblypygi, Charinidae). Zoologischer Anzeiger 244: 239 - 247. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2006.01.002" title="Courtship and sperm transfer in Charinus neocaledonicus Kraepelin, 1895 and Charinus australianus (L. Koch, 1867) (Arachnida, Amblypygi, Charinidae)" type="journal article" year="2006">Weygoldt 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
